<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- Times Mirror Co.:
   Vice President Is Appointed
   For the Newspaper Group
</HL>
<DATE>
09/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS TMC
</CO>
<IN>
MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)
</IN>
<LP>
   Richard T. Schlosberg III, 46 years old, was elected group
vice president-newspapers of Times Mirror Co., Los Angeles.
Duties related to that post had been split among several
executives since 1988.
   Mr. Schlosberg will become the media company's third group
vice president when he assumes his new post later this month.
He also will be chairman of the newspaper management
committee with responsibility for six company newspapers, and
for group advertising sales, newsprint purchases and other
newspaper matters.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Schlosberg has been president of the Los Angeles Times
newspaper since 1988. A successor hasn't been named.
   Donald F. Wright, 56, senior vice president, assumed added
responsibility for various financial and administrative
functions of Times Mirror, including budget and planning. He
relinquishes responsibility to Mr. Schlosberg for four
newspapers. He continues to oversee the company's broadcast
and cable television groups.
</TEXT>
